  "decision_conditions": [
    "The development to which this permission relates must be commenced not later than three years from the date of this permission.",
    "Reason:-",
    "To comply with the requirements of Section 91 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended by Section 51 of the Planning and Compulsory Purchase Act 2004).",
    "Before any of the dwellings hereby approved are occupied details of cycle storage, refuse and recycling storage and collection and car parking spaces shall be provided in writing to the local planning authority. The details shall be implemented in accordance to the approved scheme prior to the occupation of any part of the development and retained as such thereafter.",
    "Reason;",
    "in the interest of the visual amenity of the site and the highway safety.",
    "The proposed development hereby approved shall be constructed in accordance with the materials detailed under on the approved plan as annotated unless otherwise agreed in writing by the Local Planning Authority.",
    "Reason: To ensure that the appearance of the proposed development will harmonise with the character of the surrounding area and comply with Policy DC61 of the Development Control Policies Development Plan Document",
    "The development hereby permitted shall not be carried out otherwise than in complete accordance with the approved plans (as set out on page one of this decision notice).",
    "Reason:-",
    "For the avoidance of doubt and to ensure that the development is carried out as approved.",
    "Statement Required by Article 35 (2) of the Town and Country Planning (Development Management Procedure) (England) Order 2015: In accordance with paragraph 38 of the National Planning Policy Framework 2018, improvements required to make the proposal acceptable were negotiated with the applicant in meetings, through emails and telephone calls. The revisions involved the improvement to design, layout and quality of dwellings. The amendments were subsequently submitted in early February.",
    "Notwithstanding the drawing hereby approved, the scheme only relates to the 6 number dwelling at the roof of the existing building and it would not relate to any other blocks on the site which would be subject to separate planning application whatsoever.",
